{"word":"H3895 - לְחִי - lᵉchîy - lekh-ee' - Cheek","slug":"H3895","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">לְחִי</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lᵉchîy"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>lekh-ee'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cheek"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DC;&#x05D7;&#x05D9; - l<sup>e</sup>ch&#x0131;&#x0302;y</b> - <i>lekh-ee'</i><p/>From an unused root meaning to <i>be soft</i>; the <i>cheek</i> (from its <i>fleshiness</i>); hence the <i>jaw</i> bone: - cheek (bone), jaw (bone)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3896\">H3896</a>"}]}